Thanks to the San Mateo County Elections Office and Chief Elections Officer Mark Church for demonstrating the county’s new voting machines in San Mateo. Proud that San Mateo County is moving forward in this area! @smcvote #SanMateoCounty

After legislative programming on cable is maintained as a short term fix, I welcome a broader discussion of how to make CA a model of “digital democracy” with access to content created as part of public business in the Capitol. TY @CASOSvote for preserving #CalChannel archives.

Preserving gavel-to-gavel legislative programming on cable presents some technical challenges within the Capitol building, but it’s the right thing to do in the interest of transparency and democracy. I look forward to working with cable companies and others to ensure continuity.

CA’s cable companies have shut down #CalChannel. I’m working with parties to preserve legislative programming (available on-line too) when session resumes in January for CA’s 6 million cable households. State law (DIVCA) requires companies to air this programming upon request.
